cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT 

This paper focuses on the use of unmanned aerial vehicles (UAVs) to assist in vehicular networks, which involves communication and mobility aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves optimization of the UAV's flight path, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). The use of deep reinforcement learning for optimization suggests the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves decision-making and control, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper involves information theory aspects related to maximizing throughput, which falls under the category of cs.IT (Information Theory).
